Global Wrist worn Pulse Oximetry Market Insights
Wrist worn Pulse Oximetry Market size was valued at USD 0.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 1.2 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 12% from 2024 to 2030.

Wrist Worn Pulse Oximetry Market Overview
The wrist-worn pulse oximetry market is experiencing rapid growth, driven by increasing demand for non-invasive, continuous health monitoring devices. In 2023, the global market was valued at approximately USD 2.5 billion and is projected to reach USD 6.4 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 14.5%. The adoption of wrist-worn pulse oximeters is being fueled by advancements in wearable technology, rising health awareness, and the growing prevalence of chronic diseases. This market is expected to expand significantly due to innovations in sensor technology and the increasing need for home healthcare solutions, along with the rising geriatric population worldwide.

